### Workstream B — QAV250 Physical Parameter Measurement (Member 2)

**What:** Measure the real drone and produce accurate parameter values.

**Tasks:**
- [ ] Weigh the fully assembled QAV250 with battery (→ `params.mass`)
- [ ] Measure motor-to-center arm length (→ `params.arm_len`)
- [ ] Estimate moment of inertia — options:
  - Bifilar pendulum test (best if time permits)
  - CAD estimate from component masses + distances
  - Use datasheet approximations for similar frames
- [ ] Motor characterization for 2207 KV1950 + 5" props:
  - Thrust coefficient `kT`: from motor datasheet thrust tables, or bench test if thrust stand available
  - Torque coefficient `kQ`: estimate as `kQ ≈ kT × prop_pitch_factor`
  - Motor time constant `motor_tc`: typically 20-40 ms for BLHeli_S ESCs
- [ ] Verify motor mapping / numbering (PX4 X-configuration convention)
- [ ] Update `simulink/params/qav250_params.m` with all measured values
- [ ] Calculate expected hover throttle from parameters: `throttle_hover = mass × g / (4 × kT × ω²)`

**Depends on:** Physical access to the drone + scale + measuring tools  
**Feeds into:** D1 (plant model), Workstream A (sim parameters), Workstream C (known baseline for comparison)

