### Workstream C — MoCap Setup + Flight Testing (Member 3)

**What:** Get OptiTrack working with PX4 and fly the drone in the cage for data collection.

**Architecture:**
```
OptiTrack Cameras → Motive (NatNet) → Python Bridge → MAVLink → Pixhawk 6C
                                              ↕ (UDP forwarding)
                                             QGC (arm, monitor, emergency stop)
```

**No RC controller required.** PX4 is configured to arm from QGC only (`COM_RC_IN_MODE = 4`).
QGC connects through the Python bridge via UDP, maintaining full functionality.

**Bridge script location:** `scripts/mocap_bridge/optitrack_bridge.py`
**Bridge setup guide:** `scripts/mocap_bridge/README.md`

**Tasks:**

_OptiTrack Setup:_
- [ ] Attach ≥4 reflective markers to QAV250 in asymmetric arrangement
- [ ] Create rigid body in Motive (select markers → right-click → Rigid Body → Create)
- [ ] Note the rigid body ID (default = 1, shown in Properties panel)
- [ ] Enable streaming: View → Data Streaming Pane → Broadcast Frame Data = ON (Multicast)
- [ ] Note Motive coordinate frame convention (default: Y-up) — needed for `--frame` flag

_PX4 Configuration (set in QGC → Vehicle Setup → Parameters):_
- [ ] Calibrate sensors: Accelerometer (6-position), Gyroscope, Level Horizon
- [ ] Set all PX4 parameters from table below → reboot Pixhawk

_Bridge + QGC:_
- [ ] Install Python deps on Motive PC: `pip install pymavlink pyserial`
- [ ] Identify Pixhawk COM port (Device Manager → Ports → look for "PX4 FMU")
- [ ] Close QGC
- [ ] Run bridge: `python optitrack_bridge.py --com COMx`
- [ ] Reopen QGC → Application Settings → Comm Links → Add UDP → port 14551 → Connect
- [ ] Verify: bridge prints NED position, QGC shows correct position when drone is moved by hand

_Flight Testing:_
- [ ] Test 1 — Hover: Arm from QGC, takeoff to 1m, hover 15s, land (verify stability)
- [ ] Test 2 — Altitude step: hover 1m → step to 1.5m → hold 10s → return
- [ ] Test 3 — Lateral step: hover 1m → step right 0.5m → hold 10s → return
- [ ] Test 4 — Forward step: hover 1m → step forward 0.5m → hold 10s → return
- [ ] Record video of each test from fixed camera position
- [ ] Start/stop Motive recording for each test (File → label each take)

_Data Collection:_
- [ ] Download `.ulg` flight logs: QGC → Analyze Tools → Log Download → Refresh → Download
- [ ] Export OptiTrack `.csv`: Motive → File → Export Tracking Data → CSV (Rigid Bodies, Global coords)
- [ ] Transfer video recordings
- [ ] Label everything: `Test1_Hover.ulg`, `Test1_Hover.csv`, `Test1_Hover.mp4`, etc.

**PX4 Parameters (set ALL of these in QGC before flying):**

| Parameter | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `EKF2_EV_CTRL` | `15` | Fuse position + velocity + yaw from vision |
| `EKF2_HGT_REF` | `3` (Vision) | Use MoCap for altitude reference |
| `EKF2_EV_DELAY` | `10` | Pipeline latency in ms |
| `EKF2_EVP_NOISE` | `0.01` | Position noise (m) — OptiTrack is very accurate |
| `EKF2_EVA_NOISE` | `0.01` | Attitude noise (rad) |
| `EKF2_MAG_TYPE` | `5` | Disable magnetometer (use MoCap heading instead) |
| `COM_ARM_MAG_STR` | `-1` | Disable mag strength check |
| `COM_RC_IN_MODE` | `4` | No RC stick input (arm from QGC only) |
| `NAV_RCL_ACT` | `1` (Hold) | Hold position on RC loss (won't trigger since RC disabled) |
| `COM_ARM_WO_GPS` | `1` | Allow arming without GPS (we use MoCap instead) |

> **Hardware setup:** Pixhawk 6C connected to Motive PC via USB. No telemetry radio or RC controller needed.

**What the .ulg log contains (used for behavior matching):**
- `actuator_outputs` — timestamped motor PWM commands (this is what we replay in SITL)
- `vehicle_local_position` — PX4's position estimate
- `vehicle_attitude` — PX4's attitude estimate (quaternion)
- `sensor_combined` — raw IMU readings (accel + gyro)

**After flight:** Extract motor commands from `.ulg`, replay through Simulink `Quad_UAV_Dynamics` in normal mode, compare simulated vs OptiTrack ground truth → behavior matching (D2).

**Depends on:** Drone cage access, OptiTrack system running, Python 3.7+ on Motive PC  
**Feeds into:** D2 (real flight data for comparison), D4 (flying drone demo)

